<HL>
   Business Brief -- Harrisons &amp; Crosfield PLC:
   Firm to Acquire Crossley
   From Bowater Industries
</HL>
<DATE>
05/11/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9B
</SO>
<CO>
   U.HRS BWTRY
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
BUILDING MATERIALS (BLD)
</IN>
<LP>
   Harrisons &amp; Crosfield PLC, a U.K. chemicals, building
supplies and trading company, said it will acquire building
materials supplier Crossley Builders' Merchants Ltd. for
about #113 million ($189.8 million) from Bowater Industries
PLC.
   Harrisons &amp; Crosfield said it plans to finance the
acquisition through a 1-for-5 rights issue meant to raise
#147 million. The company will be issuing a total of
113,919,796 new ordinary shares for 132 pence ($2.22) a
share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Additionally, the company forecast a 17% increase in its
full-year dividend for fiscal 1989. It said it intends to
propose a final payout of nine pence a share, compared with
the 7.7 pence in fiscal 1988.
   Harrisons &amp; Crossfield said the pending purchase fits into
an acquisition pattern recently established to enhance growth
in its core businesses.
</TEXT>
